at question. If the member wants further guidance on this, I refer him to Speaker's rulings 191/3 and 191/4.</p><p class="SupQuestion"><strong>Jacinda Ardern</strong>: Is she telling parents like Ebony Andrews, who, despite stringent budgeting, is left with $80 a week from her income as a learning support teacher and has to rely on KidsCan to provide basics like food, clothing, and shoes for her family, that she has all the money she needs to get by, or is she telling her that she is a bad parent?</p><p class="SupAnswer"><strong>Hon JUDITH COLLINS</strong>: No, what I am saying to that person who is now being quoted by Miss Ardern is that I do not agree with the Labour Party, or with Mr Stuart Nash, who today said that poverty causes crime. I do not believe that.</p></div></body>
